At about 1:15 he explains that The Exorcist was about the mystery of faith. It's not a horror film. It reminds me of the fairly grotesque Passion of the Christ by Mel Gibson. 

I truly have a difficult time comprehending the proclivity for brutality that these films seem to portray as religious imagery. 